19 Chapter 5. Disciplinary Proceedings; Enforcement
20 Sec. 1. The board may take disciplinary action against a licensee
21 for any of the following violations:
22 (1) Violating this article or rules adopted by the board under
23 this article.
24 (2) Making a false or materially misleading representation:
25 (A) in a license application form or renewal form; or
26 (B) in information provided to the board.
27 (3) Failing to pay fees or fines required under this article.
28 (4) Communicating to the public false or misleading
29 information concerning the license held.
30 (5) Failing to complete the continuing education requirements
31 established by the board.
32 Sec. 2. The board's conduct of disciplinary hearings is governed
33 by the procedures set forth in IC 4-21.5.
34 Sec. 3. The board may summarily suspend a license for up to
35 ninety (90) days before a final adjudication or during an appeal of
36 the board's determination if the board finds that the licensee
37 represents a clear and immediate danger to the public's health,
38 safety, or property if the licensee is allowed to engage in the actions
39 permitted by the license held. The summary suspension may be
40 renewed, upon a hearing before the board, for up to ninety (90)
41 days.
42 Sec. 4. (a) When the board determines that an individual not
2026 IN 1236—LS 6915/DI 153

11
1 licensed under this article is engaged in or believed to be engaged
2 in activities for which a license is required under this article, the
3 board may issue an order to that individual requiring the
4 individual to show cause why the individual should not be ordered
5 to cease and desist from such activities. The show cause order must
6 set forth a time and place for a hearing at which the affected
7 individual may appear and show cause as to why the individual
8 should not be subject to licensing under this article.
9 (b) If the board, after a hearing, determines that the activities
10 in which the individual is engaged are subject to licensing under
11 this article, the board may issue a cease and desist order that
12 describes the individual and the activities that are the subjects of
13 the order.
14 (c) A cease and desist order issued under this section is
15 enforceable in the circuit or superior courts.
16 Sec. 5. An individual who:
17 (1) engages in or offers to engage in activities that require a
18 license under this article and is not licensed or exempt from
19 licensing;
20 (2) presents as the individual's own the license of another;
21 (3) intentionally gives false or materially misleading
22 information of any kind to the board or to a board member in
23 connection with licensing matters;
24 (4) impersonates another licensee; or
25 (5) uses an expired, suspended, or revoked license;
26 commits a Class B misdemeanor.
27 Sec. 6. The following are entitled to judicial review under
28 IC 4-21.5:
29 (1) An individual who applies for and is denied a license.
30 (2) A licensee who is aggrieved by an order or a determination
31 of the board.
32 Sec. 7. The attorney general shall act as the legal adviser for the
33 board and provide any legal assistance necessary to carry out this
34 article.
